<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>DutchNews.nl</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/</link><description>DutchNews.nl brings daily news from The Netherlands in English</description><lastBuildDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 10:08:27 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Students still opt for the wrong courses or aim too high</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/students-still-opt-for-the-wrong-courses-or-aim-too-high/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238749 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-education category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Students still opt for the wrong courses or aim too high</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-29T10:08:27+00:00"> July 29, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-206905" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_206905"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Depositphotos_163796742_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Depositphotos_163796742_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Depositphotos_163796742_S-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Depositphotos_163796742_S-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Depositphotos_163796742_S-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Depositphotos_163796742_S-640x427.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Depositphotos_163796742_S-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Depositphotos_163796742_S-130x87.jpg 130w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-206905"> The library at Delft University. Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Students are not always opting for the course that is best for them, leading to high dropout figures and a lack of professionals in other sectors that are currently struggling, a government <a href="https://open.overheid.nl/documenten/85e9ab6b-8aea-4231-a901-7e8259e4093a/file">report</a> into the efficiency of higher education has said.</p><p>In the 2021-2022 academic year some 30% of first year hbo and university students either dropped out or switched course, a figure that has remained more or less the same over the years. Around 34% of first year hbo students quit compared to 25% of first year university students.</p><p>Stricter selection for courses with a high drop-out rate could be part of the solution, as well as a compulsory “taster period” and higher fees for master’s degrees, the report said.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The report said the move away from “academic drift” where students choose university over more practical education, even if they would be better suited to the type of studies offered there, is a very difficult one to engineer.</p><p>But the current situation will lead to fewer professionals in sectors where they are needed most, such as teaching, healthcare and the technical professions, the report said.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Policies must also be aimed at encouraging international students to stay in the country, the researchers said, for instance by enabling them to learn Dutch.</p><p>At the moment some 24% of international students are still living and working in the Netherlands five years after concluding their studies. Students from outside the EU are more likely to stay than EU students, at 38% and 18% respectively.</p><p>The new government, however, wants to cut the number of foreign students drastically.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/education/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238749</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 10:08:27 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Pro-Palestine campaigners throw red paint at Amsterdam palace</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/pro-palestine-campaigners-throw-red-paint-at-amsterdam-palace/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238756 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-amsterdam category-israel category-palestine category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Pro-Palestine campaigners throw red paint at Amsterdam palace</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-29T10:03:20+00:00"> July 29, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-238757" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_238757"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504523477.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504523477.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504523477-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504523477-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504523477-768x512.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-238757"> Photo: Ramon van Flymen</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The palace on Dam square in the centre of Amsterdam has been sprayed with red paint and the word “intifada” painted in yellow by pro-Palestine activists.</p><p>Cleaners were hard at work to remove the paint on Monday morning and, the building manager said, a formal police complaint has been made. “This is vandalism and that is a criminal offence,” he told broadcaster NOS.</p><p>Campaign group Palestine Action spread photos of the damage on social media. The message, they said, is directed at the Dutch government, saying the red paint “symbolises the blood of Palestinians flowing through the streets of Gaza”.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Earlier this month there was a similar paint attack on Rotterdam’s council offices.</p><p>The palace, once called the “eighth wonder” of the world, was built in the 17<sup>th</sup> century as Amsterdam’s city hall. It’s roof and façade are currently undergoing a major renovation.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/amsterdam/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/israel/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/palestine/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238756</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 10:03:20 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Finance ministry says no to extra funding for crypto regulation</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/finance-ministry-says-no-to-extra-funding-for-crypto-regulation/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238748 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-banking category-business category-cryptocurrency"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Finance ministry says no to extra funding for crypto regulation</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-29T08:54:34+00:00"> July 29, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-197228" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_197228"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 999px) 100vw, 999px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Depositphotos_189700870_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Depositphotos_189700870_S.jpg 999w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Depositphotos_189700870_S-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Depositphotos_189700870_S-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Depositphotos_189700870_S-768x513.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Depositphotos_189700870_S-640x427.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Depositphotos_189700870_S-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Depositphotos_189700870_S-130x87.jpg 130w" width="999"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-197228"> Mining crypto currencies. Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The finance ministry has turned down several requests from the Dutch financial sector watchdog AFM for additional funding to monitor the crypto currency sector, the <a href="https://fd.nl/financiele-markten/1523657/ministerie-van-financien-zet-rem-op-cryptotoezicht-afm">Financieele Dagblad</a> reported on Monday.</p><p>In addition, the ministry has placed limits on the contributions that the AFM can ask from the sector itself, the paper said, quoting government documents obtained using freedom of information legislation.</p><p>The AFM says it needs additional funding to meet new responsibilities which derive from EU legislation on the crypto currency sector. But the ministry says a government contribution would be “politically unachievable” and wants instead a minimum level of regulation, which the AFM says is insufficient to allow it to do an effective job.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The documents, almost 300 pages in total, show that the finance ministry is not as concerned about fraud involving crypto as the AFM. “Given the risks in the crypto sector… we advice going for the minimum scenario”, the paper quotes one document as saying.</p><p>Experts and the Trimbos addiction centre are surprised by the ministry’s reluctance, telling the paper this will result in “sub-optimal supervision”.</p><p>The <a href="https://www.esma.europa.eu/esmas-activities/digital-finance-and-innovation/markets-crypto-assets-regulation-mica">EU legislation, known as MiCa</a>, comes into effect at the end of this year.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The AFM told the paper it will focuses “on those issues where the most harm to consumers, investors and market participants exists or may arise,” and declined to comment on the finance ministry’s stance.</p><p>A spokesman for ministry said that the required capacity was determined and allocated in close consultation with the regulators and said there will be a review next year.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/banking/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/cryptocurrency/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238748</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 08:54:34 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Randstad founder Frits Goldschmeding dies at the age of 90</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/randstad-founder-frits-goldschmeding-dies-at-the-age-of-90/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238743 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Randstad founder Frits Goldschmeding dies at the age of 90</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-29T08:24:06+00:00"> July 29, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-97268" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_97268"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Frits-Goldschmeding.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Frits-Goldschmeding.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Frits-Goldschmeding-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Frits-Goldschmeding-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Frits-Goldschmeding-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Frits-Goldschmeding-300x200.jpg 300w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-97268"> Frits Goldschmeding in his study. Photo: Marijn Alders/Hollandse Hoogte</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Frits Goldschmeding, the founder of staffing agency Randstad, has died at the age of 90, the </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.randstad.com/press/2024/in-memoriam-frits-goldschmeding/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">company he founded</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> nearly 65 years ago said on Monday. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Goldschmeding set up Randstad, then known as Uitzendbureau Amstelveen while a student, with him and a fellow student each investing 500 guilders. It was a golden idea, focusing first on students and later on married women who wanted a part-time job.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">In 1963 new locations opened in Leiden and Rotterdam and the company name was changed to Randstad. The first foreign branch opened in 1965 in Brussels and by the end of the 1970s, the company had over 100 branches. </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">In 1990, Randstad was floated on the Amsterdam </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">stock exchange</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">. This was not for money but to get the name better known because of the shortage of good managers, Goldschmeding said at the time. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">For years Goldschmeding was the richest man in the Netherlands and he put much of his money to good use, sponsoring a research </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">centre</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> at Nyenrode and funding the construction of Golden Age clipper Stad Amsterdam as an employment project. </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>He retired from the company he founded in 2011 and i<span data-preserver-spaces="true">n 2015 he established the Goldschmeding Foundation, a philanthropic foundation dedicated to improving the way people work and cooperate.<br/> </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">In 2016, he told the </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://fd.nl/bedrijfsleven/1525280/rijkste-man-van-nederland-vergat-de-maatschappij-nooit" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Financieele Dagblad</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> that he had no problem letting his money go. “If you worked for it, you did not do it alone,” he said. “So I give it </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">away,</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> because in a way it is not mine.” </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Last year Goldschmeding was in third place in the Quote rich list, with </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">estimated</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> worth of €5.8 billion. Randstad itself is the world’s </span>largest staffing agency, with approximately 40,000 employees in 39 countries and annual revenue of € 25.4 billion in 2023.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238743</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 08:24:06 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>PostNL cuts the number of orange post boxes as letters decline</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/postnl-cuts-the-number-of-orange-post-boxes-as-letters-decline/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238734 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> PostNL cuts the number of orange post boxes as letters decline</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-29T07:50:07+00:00"> July 29, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-139495" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_139495"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="669" sizes="(max-width: 889px) 100vw, 889px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/postnl-postbox.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/postnl-postbox.jpg 889w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/postnl-postbox-560x421.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/postnl-postbox-768x578.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/postnl-postbox-640x482.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/postnl-postbox-93x70.jpg 93w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/postnl-postbox-130x98.jpg 130w" width="889"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-139495"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>PostNL is removing 300 of its 11,000 orange post boxes because they are underused.</p><p>The locations of the disappearing post boxes have been carefully selected, so as not to be in breach of the postal law, a spokesman for the company told broadcaster NOS.</p><p>The company is legally obliged to collect and deliver post within a certain time limit, which means there must be a post box within one kilometre in areas with more than 5,000 people and within 2.5 kilometres in areas with fewer than 5,000.</p><p>“If there are no or very few cards and letters in the box, it is a waste of time and money,” the spokesman told the broadcaster.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>PostNL said it has discussed the matter with local councils and organisations for the elderly. In places where people are still in the habit of sending post, such as near hospitals or care homes, nothing will change.</p><p>“We have been doing this for 225 years and we know from experience how much use a post box gets,” the spokesman said.</p><p>At the same time, PostNL is putting up more <a href="https://www.postnl.nl/locatiewijzer/?f=36">automatic parcel drop off and pick up points</a>, to cope with the shift from letters to parcel post. Many of these also have slits for letters.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>“People can pick up or drop off parcels and letters in their own time. The lockers are being put in strategic places, including in villages,” the spokesman said.</p><p>The first post boxes will go in Noord-Holland, Friesland and Groningen at the end of August.</p><p>PostNL also wants to <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/04/postnl-wants-to-reduce-mail-deliveries-to-every-other-day/">reduce deliveries</a> to every other day because there is too little post and too few delivery workers to run a five-day operation. It also <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/price-of-a-stamp-goes-up-again-to-e1-14/">put up</a> the price of stamps to €1.14.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238734</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 07:50:07 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>A summery week ahead, but rain will be back by the weekend</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/a-summery-week-ahead-but-rain-will-be-back-by-the-weekend/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238735 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-society category-wadden-sea category-weather"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> A summery week ahead, but rain will be back by the weekend</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-29T07:43:40+00:00"> July 29, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-238737" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_238737"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1920" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/IMG_7025-scaled.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/IMG_7025-scaled.jpg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/IMG_7025-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/IMG_7025-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/IMG_7025-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/IMG_7025-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/IMG_7025-2048x1536.jpg 2048w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-238737"> Enjoying the summer sunshine on Vlieland. Photo: Dutch News</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The Netherlands is set for at least two warm, sunny days to kick off the week, but there may be occasional showers and cloud again by Wednesday.</p><p>According to the KNMI weather bureau, Monday and Tuesday will have blue skies and sunshine, with temperatures as high as 27° in sheltered places.</p><p>Wednesday will be warmer still but there will be more cloud and a 30% chance of rain, the KNMI weather bureau said. Thursday will be slightly warmer and rain is more likely. There is a similar picture up to and including the weekend although the sunshine will be less frequent from Friday.</p><p>Heading into the second week of August, the temperature will drop again to the low 20s, which is normal for the time of year. Rain will also be more likely, but there will also be plenty of sunshine, the KNMI said.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/wadden-sea/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/weather/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238735</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 07:43:40 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>No Dutch Olympic medals yet despite enthusiastic royal support</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/no-dutch-olympic-medals-yet-despite-enthusiastic-royal-support/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238730 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-olympics category-royals category-sport"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> No Dutch Olympic medals yet despite enthusiastic royal support</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-29T07:33:36+00:00"> July 29, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-238731" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_238731"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504446264.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504446264.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504446264-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504446264-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504446264-768x512.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-238731"> Princess Amalia, queen Maxima,and king Willem-Alexander roar on Puck Pieterse. Photo: Robin Utrecht ANP</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Two “official” days into the Olympics and the Netherlands has yet to make a mark on the medals table following a disappointing weekend.</p><p>The biggest disappointment of the weekend was mountain biker Puck Pieterse, who seemed sure of at least the silver medal <a href="https://cyclinguptodate.com/mountain-bike/i-should-have-gotten-silver-today-olympic-heartbreak-for-puck-pieterse-after-late-puncture-in-womens-mountain-bike">when a flat tyre</a> put paid to her hopes. She managed to climb back up to fourth place, egged on by cheering Dutch royals.</p><p>In the archery competition, the Dutch team could only manage fourth place, and swimmer Arno Kamminga also ended just outside the medals in the 100 metres crawl.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The last time the Dutch team failed to win a medal over the opening weekend was in 1996 during the Atlanta games.</p><p>Today’s highlights featuring Dutch hopefuls include Tallon Griekspoor taking on Carlos Alcaraz in the tennis singles second round (7 pm) and the Dutch women’s hockey team and defending champions, against Germany (7.45 pm).</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/olympics/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/royals/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/sport/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238730</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 07:33:36 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Applications to bring non-EU workers into the Netherlands soar</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/applications-to-bring-non-eu-workers-into-the-netherlands-soar/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238727 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-immigration category-jobs"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Applications to bring non-EU workers into the Netherlands soar</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-29T07:04:44+00:00"> July 29, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-204110" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_204110"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="668" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Depositphotos_380878314_S.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Depositphotos_380878314_S.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Depositphotos_380878314_S-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Depositphotos_380878314_S-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Depositphotos_380878314_S-768x513.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Depositphotos_380878314_S-640x428.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Depositphotos_380878314_S-92x62.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Depositphotos_380878314_S-130x87.jpg 130w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-204110"> Photo: Depositphotos.com</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The government jobs agency UWV received 18,800 requests from Dutch firms to bring in workers from <a href="https://www.uwv.nl/werkgevers/werkvergunning/twv-aanvragen/detail/voorwaarden-voor-twv">outside the EU</a> in the first six months of this year, just 2,000 below the total for 2023.</p><p>So many requests are now pending that firms have been warned the five week deadline for processing will not be met, the <a href="https://www.nu.nl/economie/6322203/arbeidsmigratie-van-buiten-de-eu-groeit-hard.html">UWV told news website Nu.nl</a>.</p><p>Companies who wish to bring in someone from <a href="https://www.government.nl/topics/foreign-citizens-working-in-the-netherlands">outside the EU</a> to do a specific job have to have a permit from the UWV to do so.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The surge in applications has been prompted by the shortage of skilled workers in some sectors of the Dutch economy. There are currently some 450,000 open vacancies, according to national statistics agency CBS.</p><p>The number of refugees with a work permit has also soared from 2,000 last year to 5,600 in the first six months of 2024. Refugees are now able to work more than the regulation 24 weeks following a <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2023/11/council-of-state-rules-asylum-seekers-can-work-beyond-24-weeks/">court ruling last November</a>.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/immigration/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/jobs/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238727</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Jul 2024 07:04:44 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Police remove children who made 112 distress call</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/police-remove-children-who-made-112-distress-call/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238723 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-children category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Police remove children who made 112 distress call</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-27T16:37:15+00:00"> July 27, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-227530" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_227530"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1333" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L.jpg 2000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-1200x800.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/Depositphotos_497136744_L-1536x1024.jpg 1536w" width="2000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-227530"> Photo: Depositphotos</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Police removed four children from their home in Tilburg at the weekend when one of them called emergency number 112 to say they were worried about their father, local broadcaster <a href="https://www.omroepbrabant.nl/nieuws/4516738/kinderen-bellen-112-voor-vader-agenten-schrikken-van-wat-ze-zien-in-huis">Omroep Brabant</a> reported.</p><p>Officer at the scene Mandy van Os took to <a href="https://www.instagram.com/p/C95fcGAIcO0/">Instagram</a> to describe the house as “a complete mess, with no clean clothes for the children.” The youngest two, who slept on improvised beds, hadn’t eaten in 24 hours and there was just mouldy food in the fridge, she said.</p><p>The children, whose ages were not made public, have been taken into care while social service are investigating the situation. It is not known how the father of the children is doing.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/children/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238723</guid><pubDate>Sat, 27 Jul 2024 16:37:15 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Outlets want to sell drinks but do not care for the empties: NOS</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/outlets-want-to-sell-drinks-but-do-not-care-for-the-empties-nos/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238706 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-environment category-recycling category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Outlets want to sell drinks but do not care for the empties: NOS</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-26T11:47:02+00:00"> July 26, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-229278" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_229278"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1512" sizes="(max-width: 2016px) 100vw, 2016px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_5021.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_5021.jpg 2016w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_5021-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_5021-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_5021-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/IMG_5021-1536x1152.jpg 1536w" width="2016"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-229278"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Places which sell drinks as part of their services, such as cinemas, kiosks and amusement parks, are against a legal obligation to take in empty bottles and cans if recycling targets are not met, broadcaster <a href="https://nos.nl/artikel/2530271-verkooppunten-van-flesjes-en-blikjes-willen-geen-verplichting-tot-inname">NOS</a> said on Friday.</p><p>Targets for recycling plastic bottles and cans were not reached last year for the second year in a row, according to Verpact, the industry body charged with dealing with recyclable waste.</p><p>A year after deposits were introduced on cans, just 65% were being handed into collection points, as were 68% of bottles, Verpact said. The official target is 90%.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The low return rates mean some <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/04/e374-million-unclaimed-as-can-and-bottle-recycling-misses-target/">€374 million</a> in deposits was not collected by consumers. The Netherlands introduced deposits of 15 cents on small bottles in July 2021. Cans followed last April.</p><p>For the targets to be met, some 8,000 extra collection points would be needed, Verpact said but so far only 800 have been added, causing a substantial litter problem.</p><p>A legal requirement for drinks sellers to take in empties would help, local councils, rubbish collection services and environmental organisations have said.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Government documents requested by NOS show that such a requirement, already in place in Germany, was considered but rejected for reasons that remained unclear.</p><p>The environmental inspectorate Leefomgeving en Transport has said that if drinks manufacturers do not do more to promote collection they will be <a href="https://nos.nl/artikel/2528562-statiegeldsysteem-moet-beter-inspectie-dreigt-met-dwangsommen-van-ruim-300-miljoen">fined</a> up to €300 million.</p><p>The government will evaluate the legal framework for the deposit scheme later this year.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/environment/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/recycling/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238706</guid><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jul 2024 11:47:02 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>